Notebook[{
Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["SIRCm model: equilibrium and stability analysis\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n1. ",
 StyleBox["Quick context:\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "This is a modified SIRC epidemiological model where the cross-immunity \
erosion rates are driven by infection prevalence rather than being fixed \
constants\n\nIn the original SIRC:  \[Delta] (R\[Rule]C rate) and \[Gamma] (C\
\[Rule]S rate) are constants.\n\nIn our modification (SIRCm):\n\[Bullet] \
\[Delta] = \[Delta]\[Prime] \[CenterDot] \[Beta] S I\n\[Bullet] \[Gamma] = \
\[Gamma]\[Prime] \[CenterDot] \[Beta] S I\n\nWhere \[Beta]  is the contact \
rate, S is the proportion of susceptible people and I is the proportion of \
infected/infective people. All together, \[Beta] S I represents the infection \
incidence.\n\nThe motivation is that mutations arise proportionally to the \
number of active infections, since  each replication event is an opportunity \
for mutation. \n\nThe constants \[Delta]\[Prime] and \[Gamma]\[Prime]  are \
expressed in this notebook as \[Delta]p and \[Gamma]p \n\n2. ",
 StyleBox["Parameter Restrictions:\n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "All parameters are positive by biological definition:\n\[Bullet] \[Mu] > 0 \
: birth/death rate (demographic turnover)\n\[Bullet] \[Beta] > 0 : contact \
rate\n\[Bullet] \[Alpha] > 0 : recovery rate. (its inverse is the average \
time spent in the I compartment) \n\[Bullet] \[Sigma] \[Element] (0, 1) : \
cross-immunity factor (0 = full immunity, 1 = none)\n",
 StyleBox["\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "All compartments are population fractions:\n\[Bullet] S, I, R, C \
\[GreaterEqual] 0 and S + I + R + C = 1\n",
 StyleBox["\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\[Bullet] In particular, at the endemic equilibrium: 0 < I < 1\n\n3. ",
 StyleBox["What we need:\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "In the original SIRC model, the basic reproduction number is R0 = \[Beta] / \
(\[Mu] + \[Alpha]), which represents the average number of secondary \
infections produced by a single infected individual in a fully susceptible \
population.\n\nThe system has two equilibria: a disease-free equilibrium \
(DFE) at (S, I, R, C) = (1, 0, 0, 0), and an endemic equilibrium where the \
disease persists at a positive level I > 0. A bifurcation occurs at R0 = 1: \
when R0 < 1, the DFE exists and it is stable (every small outbreak dies out). \
When R0 > 1, the endemic equilibrium emerges and is stable (the disease \
persists). \n\nWe have already verified that the DFE of the SIRCm model is \
the same to that of the original SIRC, with the same stability threshold (R0 \
< 1). This is expected because when I = 0, all infection-driven terms vanish \
and the modification has no effect.\n\nThe question now is what happens when \
R0 > 1. Does a unique endemic equilibrium exist? Is it stable? How does the \
infection-driven feedback change the bifurcation compared to the original \
SIRC?",
 StyleBox["\n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "I need help with the ",
 StyleBox["endemic equilibrium. ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "We want to... \n",
 StyleBox["\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "1. Derive the polynomial whose roots give the endemic equilibrium values of \
I (the infected fraction of the population) \n\n2. Determine whether a \
biologically meaningful root (0 < I < 1) exists and is unique when R0 > 1\n\n\
3. Analyze stability of the endemic equilibrium via the characteristic \
polynomial of the Jacobian\n\n(note: in this notebook we are using \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]II\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] as I and \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]CC\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] as C since both \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]I\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]C\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] are reserved in mathematica)\n\n\n4. ",
 StyleBox["the SIRCm model:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9888541598068323`*^9, 3.98885416068401*^9}, {
   3.9888542155502987`*^9, 3.988854465244668*^9}, {3.988854496901609*^9, 
   3.988854546487747*^9}, {3.9888547010260353`*^9, 3.988854702403919*^9}, {
   3.9888547380721617`*^9, 3.9888547384679327`*^9}, {3.9888549236439447`*^9, 
   3.9888549562870407`*^9}, 3.988855009282621*^9, {3.988855145972363*^9, 
   3.988855225395143*^9}, {3.9888553753984528`*^9, 3.988855560925077*^9}, {
   3.9888556052976217`*^9, 3.98885568573368*^9}, 3.988855732638804*^9, {
   3.9888557779071703`*^9, 3.988855787141066*^9}, {3.9888558248713217`*^9, 
   3.988855837548716*^9}, {3.988855899221077*^9, 
   3.988855918229663*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a9cc5c7e-0e17-4776-ab90-\
8250a5ed9a70"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "\"\<Global`*\>\"", "]"}], "\n"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"dS", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "*", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"1", "-", "S"}], ")"}]}], "-", 
    RowBox[{"\[Beta]", "*", "S", "*", "II"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Gamma]p", "*", "\[Beta]", "*", "S", "*", "II"}], ")"}], "*", 
     "CC"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"dI", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Beta]", "*", "S", "*", "II"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"\[Sigma]", "*", "\[Beta]", "*", "CC", "*", "II"}], "-", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "+", "\[Alpha]"}], ")"}], "*", "II"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"dR", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"1", "-", "\[Sigma]"}], ")"}], "*", "\[Beta]", "*", "CC", "*", 
     "II"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", "*", "II"}], "-", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "+", 
       RowBox[{"\[Delta]p", "*", "\[Beta]", "*", "S", "*", "II"}]}], ")"}], "*",
      "R"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"dC", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Delta]p", "*", "\[Beta]", "*", "S", "*", "II"}], ")"}], "*", 
     "R"}], "-", 
    RowBox[{"\[Beta]", "*", "CC", "*", "II"}], "-", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "+", 
       RowBox[{"\[Gamma]p", "*", "\[Beta]", "*", "S", "*", "II"}]}], ")"}], "*",
      "CC"}]}]}], ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.988855851360256*^9, 3.9888558578474913`*^9}, 
   3.988855952399609*^9, {3.988856575957082*^9, 3.9888565920666733`*^9}, 
